PLAGUE, PNEUMONIC - CONGO DR (ITURI) (04): BACKGROUND
*****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri, 25 Aug 2006
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GideonOnline [edited]
<http://www.GideonOnline.com>

The first cases of plague in this country were reported in Ituri (632 cases
during 1928 to 1959) and North Kivu (190 cases during 1938 to
1961). Plague is currently or recently endemic to Haut Zaire Province and
Ituri Sub-region (Managi Administrative Zone)
A graph of plague incidence and rates per 100 000 population in DRC is
displayed at: <http://exhibit.gideononline.com/Plague-DRC.jpg>
Note that DRC has accounted for an increasing proportion of plague cases in
Africa in recent years:
<http://exhibit.gideononline.com/Plague-Africa-DRC.jpg>
Notable outbreaks:
2004 - An outbreak (1042 suspect cases, 58 fatal) was reported in Ituri.
2005 - An outbreak (134 cases, 61 fatal) of pneumonic plague was reported
in a diamond mining area of Zobia, Kisingani.
--
Dr. Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
[ProMED thanks Dr. Berger for this Gideon information. - Mod.LL]
